{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, OFormer and CORAL fail to reconstruct the physical field, highlighting their limited generalization in low-data regimes.",
    "In this section, we assess the models' ability to generalize to finer spatial grids.",
    "For the Advection dataset, we evaluate reconstructions starting from input subsamplings of π = 20%, 50%, 100%, and query the model on denser grids with π sr = 200%, 400%, 800% of the original resolution.",
    "On the Vorticity dataset, we use the same input subsamplings but perform super-resolution only at π sr = 200% due to data availability constraints.",
    "For comparison, we also report reconstruction results at π sr = 100%, as in table 1, and present the full results in table 23."
  ]
}